FC Cartagena in-form striker Dauda Mohammed said he would not be surprised if he is invited to the Black Stars squad for the 2022 Fifa World Cup playoff double-header against West African rivals Nigeria. Ghana will play the Super Eagles in a two-legged encounter with the winner of both legs securing qualification for the global showpiece scheduled to be hosted in Qatar later this year. The four-time African champions will play host to Nigeria on March 25, 2022, before the reverse fixture at the Moshood Abiola National Stadium in Abuja on March 29, 2022.   Waldrum tip Falcons to match USA, Germany     Minister, Lagos SWAN laud Lanipekun at 80     Ojeagbase: Shaibu mourns ‘distinguished Nigerian’   The 24 year-old, who has been impressive for the Spanish second-tier side scoring 6 goals in 25 matches this season, is aiming for a Black Stars call up for the crucial games. “I believe this is my best performing season since I arrived in Europe so I will not be surprised if the technical team of the Black Stars invites me,” he told Bryt FM. “It will also be happy to join the national team to fight for qualification to the World Cup,” he added. Meanwhile, the Ghanaian ministry of Youth and Sports announced on Tuesday that only Black Stars supporters that are fully vaccinated against COVID-19 would be granted access to the Cape Coast Stadium for the crucial first leg of the playoffs.